{
  "text": "Glucocorticoid receptor (GR), is proposed to play a role in CRPC as an alternative steroid receptor for AR [CITATION_1] . Although levels of GR protein were elevated in the LNCaP95 cells (Figure 3) , the GR agonist, dexamethasone, did not affect the proliferation of the LNCaP95 cells ( Figure A1B ). This suggested that the GR is not driving proliferation in this model.",
